{
  "_id": "4b0f98ce6e778f00ea0e6c7a",
  "title": "Rate-Limited Blog API",
  "slug": "rate-limited-blog-api-medium-node-js",
  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "topics": [
    "NODE_JS"
  ],
  "statement": "Implement a RESTful API for a blog that uses rate limiting to prevent excessive requests. The API should be accessible at http://localhost:3000/. You'll need to create endpoints for creating and reading blog posts. When creating a post, the client should send a JSON object with the post title and content. When reading posts, you can return an array of all posts. The rate limit should be 5 requests per minute per IP address. If a client exceeds this limit, they should receive a 429 response with a JSON body indicating the remaining attempts within the window.",
  "constraints": [
    "Must use the express-rate-limit middleware for rate limiting",
    "Must implement rate limiting based on IP address"
  ],
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "method": "POST",
      "path": "/api/posts",
      "description": "Create a new blog post. Accepts JSON body with title and content. Returns the newly created post."
    },
    {
      "method": "GET",
      "path": "/api/posts",
      "description": "Retrieve all blog posts. Returns an array of post objects."
    }
  ],
  "mode": "solve",
  "starterCode": {
    "package.json": "{\"name\": \"blog-api\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"node index.js\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"express\": \"^4.18.2\",\n    \"express-rate-limit\": \"^5.2.0\",\n    \"json-schema\": \"^0.2.3\"\n  }\n}",
    "index.js": "const express = require('express');\nconst rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');\nconst limiter = rateLimit({\n    windowMs: 1 * 60 * 1000, // 1 minute window\n    max: 5, // limit each IP to 5 requests per windowMs\n    standardHeaders: true, // return rate limit info in the `RateLimit-*` headers\n    legacyHeaders: false, // disable the `X-RateLimit-*` headers\n    skip: (req, res) => { return false } // handle rate limit exceptions\n});\n\nconst app = express();\napp.use(express.json());\napp.use(limiter);\n\n// TODO: Implement endpoints\n\nconst PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;\napp.listen(PORT, () => console.log('Server running on port ' + PORT));"
  },
